# CodexGateway project

SwiftPM macOS menu-bar app with embedded gateway for Codex Desktop.

## Key facts

- Target: `CodexGateway/` executable, entry `main.swift` + `AppDelegate`.
- Version: `VERSION` file → `AppVersion.display`.
- Build: `make run`, `make test`, `make app`, `make release` (see `BUILDING.md`).
- Full reference: `ARCHITECTURE.md`, agent entry: `AGENTS.md`.
- GitHub repo: `rimusz/codex-bar` (unchanged).

## Identity

- Bundle ID: `com.rimusz.CodexGateway`
- Config dir: `~/.codexgateway`
- Codex provider id: `codexgateway` / `[model_providers.codexgateway]`
- Managed markers: `# >>> codexgateway managed >>>`
- Install helper resource: `codexgateway-install-update`
- Notifications: `CodexGatewayStatusChanged`, `CodexGatewayUpdateAvailable`, etc.
- Debug log: `/tmp/codexgateway_debug.log`
- UserDefaults: `codexgateway.updates.*`

## Upgrade / legacy (from CodexBar)

- Old bundle ID `com.rimusz.CodexBar` (macOS Login Items may need re-enable)
- Old config dir `~/.codexbar` → migrated on launch
- Old provider/markers `codexbar` → rewritten on refresh/patch
- Legacy release asset `CodexBar-{tag}.app.zip` still published for old updaters
- App folder migration `CodexBar.app` → `CodexGateway.app`

## When editing

- Keep changes focused; reuse existing services and notification names.
- Do not add an Xcode project; stay on SwiftPM + Makefile scripts.
- Menu bar icon: `CodexGateway/Resources/Assets.xcassets/MenuBarIcon.imageset/`.
- **Docs + tests required** with every code change — see `.cursor/rules/docs-and-tests.mdc`.
- **Always use Computer Use to test changes** after Swift/app edits (`make run` + `grokbuild-computer-use` MCP → `orca computer` → `agent-desktop` last) — see `.cursor/skills/codexgateway-dev/SKILL.md`.
- Only commit when the user explicitly asks.

